{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17488772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17488772"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:56:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:56:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"532"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"532","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/532"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.46,0.23,0.06,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"532"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66638"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"532","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/532"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-10-19T17:48:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-18T21:22:53+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2021-07-08T07:38:56+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-28 14:24:57"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"532"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9435"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52091"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"134"},{"type":"tags","id":"901"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9101"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3160"},{"type":"contributions","id":"12743"},{"type":"contributions","id":"12819"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38446"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52091"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66638","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66638"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 21-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a two day history of epigastric pain. She is normally in good health and does not take any medication apart from ibuprofen for dysmenorrhoea. Her last period finished three days ago and she was taking ibuprofen immediately prior to that. On examination she looks well, with a blood pressure of 110/70 mmHg, pulse rate of 90/min and temperature of 37.2C. She is tender in the right upper quadrant and epigastrium, but her abdomen is otherwise soft. A CT scan is performed (Images 1, 2, 3).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acute cholecystitis","Perforated peptic ulcer","Gastrointestinal stromal tumour","Carcinoma of the cardia","Acute pancreatitis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe CT shows a heterogenous mass lesion in the region of the distal stomach with an adjacent pocket of air (Image). Given the history of recent NSAID usage and the localising signs, a \u003Cstrong\u003Eperforated peptic ulcer\u003C/strong\u003E is a realistic diagnosis. Not all perforated peptic ulcers lead to generalised peritonitis and some remain localised - such as this one. A contained perforation may not have the same classical systemic symptoms/signs that are associated with free perforation. The mass lesion is an localised inflammatory reaction and collection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe gallbladder is not inflamed and there is no evidence of any inflammatory process involving the pancreas. Whilst a gastrointestinal stromal tumour is among the mass lesion to be considered, it would not contain air. A perforated neoplasm could explain this radiological appearance - but the patient is in the wrong age group for this to be a realistic diagnosis. In addition, the mass is not in the region of the cardia.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A CT scan can be very helpful in identifying a localised perforation."],"references":["Soreide K, Thorsen K, Harrison EM, et al. Perforated peptic ulcer. Lancet 2015; 386:1288-98. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26460663/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52091"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"532"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15775"},{"type":"media","id":"15776"},{"type":"media","id":"15777"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15778"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15775","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15775"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/256655ec-9a32-422a-9171-56f62dfbaf0f.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/256655ec-9a32-422a-9171-56f62dfbaf0f.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":504,"height":400}},{"type":"media","id":"15776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15776"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5b27cd77-f669-4e2f-8b5d-6230271b6e92.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5b27cd77-f669-4e2f-8b5d-6230271b6e92.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":503,"height":600}},{"type":"media","id":"15777","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15777"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/8551e7c6-6993-4d05-a8c8-eeb4b670a711.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/8551e7c6-6993-4d05-a8c8-eeb4b670a711.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":394,"height":600}},{"type":"media","id":"15778","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.